  <name>Perboric acid</name>
  <description>Perboric acid is mainly found in its salt form of sodium perborate and it can be found as a monohydrate or tetrahydrate.[A33037] It is one of the peroxy acid salts with very wide functionalities in industrial settings.[F66] Perboric acid in the form of sodium perborate is approved by Health Canada since 2004 to be used as a disinfectant of medical instruments.[L1113] By the FDA, sodium perborate is approved as an ointment for the protection of poison ivy dermatitis.[L2764]</description>
